Chernobyl nuclear explosion site and nearby ghost town of Pripyat have seen an increase in tourist interest in recent years . 
  April 26 marks the 30th anniversary of the 1986 nuclear explosion . 
  In the Exclusion Zone, visitors are banned from touching anything or eating in the area . 
  However, day trips and even overnight stays are permitted . 
  In 1986, Reactor 4 in the Chernobyl power plant exploded . 
  The explosion was one of the worst nuclear accidents in history . 
  In recent years, the area has seen a rise in dark tourism . 
 